  "description": [
    "1 WillysMotors Unit Insurance Report _By RAT WALE_ ELIGIBILITY FOR BENEFITS All benefits as described in the insurance booklet are provided present active employees with established seniority 2 Each new employee shall become eligible for the bene fits on the day he acquires seniority 30 days of work performed if actively at work on that day If such an employee is not actively at work on that day he will become insured on the day he returns to work 3 An employees eligible dependents will be insured on the day the employee becomes insured if they are properly enrolled by him or if he has no eligible dependents on the date he acquires them The following figures are the Insurance Claims week ending March 12 1961 paid in the Dept Na Number of Claims Surgical Benefits Hospital Rooms Incidentals Weekly Benefits Total Claims 5 5 A 1 103 121 126 161 165 172 175 184 185 187 190 208 209 22 233 234 242 243 262 263 263 267 268 270 275 307 308 322 324 325 329 342 346 351 355 361 362 381 382 383 401 402 403 404 423 440 441 463 504 521 540 541 542"
